<recipe>
    <name>Cucumber Salad</name>
    <indexCharacter>C</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Make the pickled mustard seeds, according to the separate recipe.

2. Make the salad. In a large bowl, combine the vinegar, honey, cucumber, onion, salt, sesame oil, and dill. Toss to coat and chill for 10 minutes. Transfer to a serving bowl, leaving some of the excess water behind. Top with fresh mint, dollops of pickled mustard seeds, if using, and a drizzle of olive oil, if desired. Season to taste and serve.</instructions>
